(1, 'Program Notes for Schumann’s Dichterliebe op.48', '12a-v2-schumann-lieder-mara-marietta.jpg', 'program-notes-for-schumann-dichterliebe-op-48', '<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"/media/django-summernote/2023-06-14/b3be5d66-a310-40f5-9e65-87afb87a45fb.png\" style=\"width: 625.773px; height: 342.219px;\"></p><p><br></p><h1 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; color: rgb(14, 45, 73); line-height: 50.4px; background-color: rgb(246, 249, 251);\">Program Notes for Schumann’s Dichterliebe op.48</h1><blockquote style=\"box-sizing: inherit; position: relative; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(14, 45, 73); background-color: rgb(246, 249, 251);\">This post is the output of the final project of the MUSC 726 Public Music Theory, which I am taking in the last semester of my Doctoral degree program. I was not very much familiar with the title of Public Music Theory. Music theory that we commonly know is a study that music students who study practical music and are active as musicians, composers, and singer-songwriters, are known to be fundamentally studied and known. However, Popular music theory is the study of how classical musicians like us can make difficult classical music easier for the audience to understand when they hold classical concerts and show them to the audience. The phrase “the popularization of classical music” has been tried by many musicians, including “Baritone Kim Dong-Gyu” and many other crossover singers and pop-opera singers. The same goes for music theory.</blockquote><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-bottom: 20px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; color: rgb(98, 111, 131); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(246, 249, 251);\">In South Korea, the newly created thing by the phase of the popularization of classical music is “the classical concerts with narrations”, and this way of classical concerts have been settled down for a long time in South Korea. For every stage, the narrator describes the work(s) to be performed at the next stage before the performer(s) present on the stage. In fact, thanks to this type of classical concert planning, it is difficult to see program notes in a detailed format in Korea unless it is a big performance such as an opera, musical performance, or large theater performance. However, venues in the United States and Europe provide booklets with program not-es for those performances. In most cases, information about the performers, staff, and performance officials and the details of the performance are written in the booklet. Even so, it doesn’t make the content of the performance as difficult as studying the audience for professionals. It’s easy to talk about, meaning that you don’t put sheet music in a performance booklet or use difficult musical terms. It depends on the level of the audience, but the audience watching the performance may or may not know how to read the score, and it may be a professor of music college.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-bottom: 20px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; color: rgb(98, 111, 131); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(246, 249, 251);\">In this context, the concept of Public Music Theory describes the form, structure, and content of the music performed by the performer for the audience in detail, and explains a little professional and deep musical theory for the audience to enjoy, making it easier and more fun for the audience to approach classical music. It is Public Music Theory that helps the audiences do it. Dichterliebe, which I am working on as a final project, is Schumann’s “Love of Poets”, which is widely known all over the world. If audiences understand not only the cultural backgrounds such as the periods that German composer Schumann lived and the weather in Germany in more detail but also the comprehension of the compositional structure in it, audiences can feel more fun when it is performed.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-bottom: 20px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; color: rgb(98, 111, 131); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(246, 249, 251);\">The problem is that among the musicians who perform this piece, there are many who don’t have enough knowledge about the work. It is difficult to say that one understood this work simply by interpreting the lyrics of the music and analyzing the score. It is that if you better understand the background of the time when composer Schumann lived and the situation of the region and culture indicated by the work, and appreciate this work, you can feel the pain of the sad and sad love of the main character in the work. In this work “The Poet’s Love”, the characteristic of the German city “Bonn” in which Schumann lived is shown. And a place called Cologne appears directly in the lyrics. If you listen carefully to a song #1 and translate the lyrics literally as it is, it is “in the beautiful May”, but why are we, moreover, “in the beautiful May”? You may ask a question why?. May is the road from spring to summer. In places like South Korea, where the four seasons are clear, summer begins and is often referred to as the changing season. May is not the only beautiful month in Korea, where weather changes are diverse, saying that May is beautiful. Some people will disagree.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-bottom: 20px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; color: rgb(98, 111, 131); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(246, 249, 251);\">However, in Germany, where you can see the sun all year round is only 4 months from May to August, and especially in Germany, when you can only face the clear and bright Sun, you dare to say that it is beautiful May. It deserves to be attached to a musical piece as a title of “Beautiful May”. How would you feel if the only time of the year that you can see the dazzling sky with clouds and clear Sun is in May? Perhaps it feels like living in a dark prison for a year and being able to see the world in just one day. That’s why Germans go out to the garden in front of their homes to sunbathe when the light shines in the sky. The lives of these Germans are expressed as lyrics in this work.</p><ul style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: rgb(246, 249, 251);\"><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(98, 111, 131); padding-left: 20px; position: relative;\">Im wunderschönen Monat Mai,</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(98, 111, 131); padding-left: 20px; position: relative;\">Als alle Knospen sprangen,</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(98, 111, 131); padding-left: 20px; position: relative;\">Da ist in meinem Herzen,</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(98, 111, 131); padding-left: 20px; position: relative;\">Die Liebe aufgegangen.</li></ul><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-bottom: 20px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; color: rgb(98, 111, 131); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(246, 249, 251);\">Does “Im wunderschönen Monat Mai(in a beautiful May)” in the lyrics above simply mean a beautiful May? As all the flowers slowly open their peaks, my love begins too. Flowers don’t only bloom in May. Love doesn’t just start in May. However, the character is having only gloomy days every day. It is difficult for love to begin in gloomy weather. As mentioned above, Germany is the only month in the year in which you can see the bright Sun. There will be no love as the dark days continue every day. Love for someone can also be compassion in some way. However, when it sees the dazzling Sun, it can develop into love. Since that time is May, I think it is the correct understanding to understand it as “in the dazzlingly beautiful May”.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-bottom: 0px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; color: rgb(98, 111, 131); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(246, 249, 251);\">Numbers 2 and 3 describe the process of developing love with beautiful things like roses, lilies, and doves. To analyze the musical composition theoretically, there is a lyric that says that love blooms like a flowering peak in a dazzlingly beautiful May on a dark chord in a minor. If Korean composers wrote songs for these lyrics, how would they have written them? Of course, since it is a dazzlingly beautiful May, you must have written the song as if it symbolizes a bright and clear May sky. However, Schumann’s Germany was not. Despite the gloomy weather, he fell in love as we could watch the dazzling sunlight seeping through. That is why the beautiful May could come out even in the dark monotone. In the 6th song of this work, I fall in love, so the statue of Our Lady resembles my love. The characteristic of Song No. 6 is that there is a part in which verse 2 to verse 3 changes from minor to major in the middle, which symbolizes that when falling in love, everything seems beautiful in this world. It might be possible to interpret such a positive feeling of love on a major scale. Song 6 is the last song in the first theme of this whole work, and it can be said that it shows the success of love and that everything looks beautiful.</p><p><br></p>', '2023-06-15 00:38:08.000000', '2023-06-15 01:08:35.375662', '2024-07-29 21:12:05.731952', 'published', 1),
(2, 'Remastered Public Music Theory for learners and teachers', 'public-music-theory.png', 'remastered-public-music-theory-learners-and-teachers', '<p style=\"text-align: center; \"><img src=\"/media/django-summernote/2023-06-15/1719e8e5-9126-493a-ac0a-cf9ac70e42a8.png\" style=\"width: 527px; height: 296.437px;\"><br></p><p>When Public Music Theory is taught by a music teacher or college professor, they bring a concept of the music theory into the public music theory and they also bring up the generalization of the music theory for the students or public to understand the concept, such as tonicization in music. </p><p>When a teacher defines a tonic, the teacher uses a home as a tonic but sometimes the home can also be multi locations such as the home of the home, so the keynote of the public music theory is how to conceptualize the theory without the usage of terminologies. </p><p>Many of the public have never ever had a professional music education, so many music teachers try to generalize the concept to understand the public. This is the beginning of public music theory.<br></p>', '2023-06-15 18:42:11.000000', '2023-06-15 18:48:12.864877', '2024-07-29 21:08:57.587591', 'published', 1),
(3, 'Music Business and Technology', 'aiformusic_5wLVMa0.jpg', 'music-business-and-technology', '<p style=\"text-align: center; \"><img src=\"/media/django-summernote/2023-06-15/c3370800-1cc3-4e70-b945-df3ed534d49e.png\" style=\"width: 500px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(68, 68, 68); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 19.2667px;\"><br></span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(68, 68, 68); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 19.2667px;\">Our Music Technology and Business program gives you hands-on experience with digital audio production and a look at the inner workings of the music industry. </span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(68, 68, 68); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 19.2667px;\">With a strong foundation in music theory fundamentals, majors will learn to create and produce digital music, use industry-standard software and hardware, and culminate with either an internship in a recording studio or performance venue, or a senior project based in the music technology or business industries.</span><br></p>', '2023-06-15 18:52:42.000000', '2023-06-15 18:55:19.764753', '2024-07-29 21:02:54.477831', 'published', 1),
(4, 'Quantum Music Theory', 'quantum-music-theory.jpg', 'quantum-music-theory', '<p><p></p><p style=\"text-align: center; \"><img src=\"/media/django-summernote/2023-06-15/3defeee9-7d2f-46f9-b111-fab707457bd9.png\" style=\"width: 512px;\"></p><h1 class=\"entry-title\" style=\"border: 0px; font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: 30px; font-weight: 800; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; clear: both; line-height: 36px; color: rgb(81, 41, 58); overflow-wrap: break-word;\">Music theory and quantum mechanics</h1>Quantum Music is a project aiming to explore the connection between music and quantum physics. The project presents quantum physics and the quantum world to a wider audience and contributes to the creation of a new musical and scientific genre - Quantum Music.</p><p>Quantum music is a project rooted in the area of quantum physics called quantum acoustics. These two, at first glance completely separate worlds — the world of quantum particles, and the world of sound that fully belongs to our reality — come into contact with one another in a series of quantum-acoustics experiments conducted in the most advanced laboratories. </p><p>During these experiments, quantum particles exhibit acoustic phenomena that can be converted into a sound that is theoretically possible to hear. The Quantum Music project enables the translation of this theoretical possibility into reality, establishing direct connections between listeners and the quantum-acoustics phenomena. The main objective of this project is to bring the imaginary principles of quantum physics closer to a wide audience through the most imaginative of all arts — music. </p><p>How do the laws of quantum physics and aesthetics of music interact? Following the universal principle of duality, we aim to answer this question by using two of the acoustically most perfect man-made concert instruments — pianos. </p><p>Two pianos will interact between themselves, with the audience and, finally, with quantum systems. To make something like this possible, it was necessary to construct original mechanisms to connect classical pianos with the world of computers, lasers and quantum physics. </p><p>The pianos equipped with such dedicated hardware and software tools become entirely new instruments — hybrid pianos, capable of interacting with the quantum world.&nbsp;<br></p>', '2023-06-15 18:56:03.000000', '2023-06-15 19:02:35.101094', '2024-07-29 20:56:14.978481', 'published', 1),
(5, 'Contemporary Music Theory', 'contemporary-music-theory.jpg', 'contemporary-music-theory', '<p style=\"text-align: center; \"><img src=\"/media/django-summernote/2023-06-15/51a49372-a523-4899-a400-12eba803d564.png\" style=\"width: 389px;\"><font face=\"open_sansregular, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 14.4px;\"><br></span></font></p><p><font face=\"open_sansregular, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 14.4px;\">Contemporary Music Theory c</span></font><span style=\"font-family: open_sansregular, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14.4px;\">overs music theory as exhibited in contemporary musical styles such as jazz, blues, rock, hip hop, funk, electronic dance music, and folk. Includes notation, pitch, meter, tonality, intervals, chord construction, and harmony. Includes basic music analysis focusing on diatonic harmonies and lead sheet notation as well as written composition. This is the first course in a three-course sequence.</span></p><h4 style=\"margin: 1.25em 0px 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: open_sanslight, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); text-rendering: optimizelegibility; line-height: 1.4; font-size: 1.85714em;\">Intended Outcomes for the course</h4><div style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: open_sansregular, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14.4px;\"><div style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.313em; padding: 0.313em 0px 0.625em; font-size: 1em; line-height: 1.6; text-rendering: auto;\">Upon completion of the course students should be able to:</p><ul style=\"margin: 0.625em 0px 0.313em 1.875em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1em; line-height: 1.6; list-style-position: outside;\"><li style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0.625em;\">Identify and notate rhythms in both simple and compound meters.</li><li style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0.625em;\">Read and write primary melodic ideas in treble and bass clefs.</li><li style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0.625em;\">Identify major and minor scales, key signatures, intervals, triads, and seventh chords.</li><li style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0.625em;\">Voice triads and seventh chords in root position and in inversion.</li><li style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0.625em;\">Compose and notate a simple melodic phrase.</li><li style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0.625em;\">Analyze simple diatonic harmonies using lead sheet symbols.</li><li style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0.625em;\">Exhibit developing musicianship by applying music theory components through musical expression.</li></ul></div></div><p><br></p>', '2023-06-15 19:05:50.000000', '2023-06-15 19:07:39.509042', '2024-07-29 20:52:02.011094', 'published', 1),
(6, 'Why Music History?', 'listening-to-history-of-classical-music.jpg', 'why-music-history', '<p style=\"text-align: center; \"><img src=\"/media/django-summernote/2023-06-15/da1b30f8-44c7-4d4d-b596-ecfec104b6ce.png\" style=\"width: 50%;\"><b><br></b></p><p style=\"text-align: center; \"><b>A Brief History of Music – From Origins to the Present Day&nbsp;</b><br></p><p><b>People learn the history enables predict and improve the future of the life and change the quality of life.</b></p><p><span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-variant-alternates: inherit; font-weight: 700; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 20px; line-height: inherit; font-family: Roboto, arial; font-optical-sizing: inherit; font-kerning: inherit; font-feature-settings: inherit; font-variation-settings: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">Music has always been an important cultural and social factor throughout human history. It helped people form tribal bonds and often served religious and spiritual needs. Music has stood the test of time from the prehistoric age till this day.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 31px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-variant-alternates: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 20px; line-height: 32px; font-family: Roboto, arial; font-optical-sizing: inherit; font-kerning: inherit; font-feature-settings: inherit; font-variation-settings: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">How did music develop throughout the centuries and around the globe? What do different cultures and generations have in common, in terms of music? What can we learn from all the different musical genres, styles, and approaches the human brain has developed throughout the years?</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 31px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-variant-alternates: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 20px; line-height: 32px; font-family: Roboto, arial; font-optical-sizing: inherit; font-kerning: inherit; font-feature-settings: inherit; font-variation-settings: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">In this article, we will shortly go through the history of music, trying to find an answer to these challenging questions. Let’s dive in!</p><p><span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-variant-alternates: inherit; font-weight: 700; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 20px; line-height: inherit; font-family: Roboto, arial; font-optical-sizing: inherit; font-kerning: inherit; font-feature-settings: inherit; font-variation-settings: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\"></span><br></p>', '2023-06-15 19:08:04.000000', '2023-06-15 19:16:33.649772', '2024-07-29 19:49:54.789940', 'published', 1),
(7, 'Music Literature for Classical Music', 'readings-for-classicalmusic.jpg', 'music-literature-classical-music', '<p><p style=\"text-align: center; \"><img src=\"/media/django-summernote/2023-06-15/f2c08af4-8c07-4559-b564-9627107910cd.png\" style=\"width: 525px;\"><br></p><p>Music literature includes Classical Music, Modern Music, Contemporary Music, POP Music, etc.</p><p>We are going to introduce Classical Music which covers specific period of music.</p><p>This course will teach you what you will learn from classical music.</p>Selected Topics in Music Literature for Non-Majors(Amateur)</p><p>What is \'classical music\'? </p><p>How did the concept(s) of classical music develop in Europe and elsewhere over the last few centuries? What roles does this music play in society today? How does \'classical music\' relate to \'other\' musics? </p><p>These questions will underpin an exploration of the values, processes, historical views, and present situations of this simultaneously specific yet ill-defined kind of music. </p><p>This course will feature listening, readings, discussions, and writing, and is open to students with all levels of musical experience.<br></p>', '2023-06-15 19:16:53.000000', '2023-06-15 19:26:01.974065', '2024-07-29 19:47:45.795563', 'published', 1),
(8, 'Special lecture All About J.S. Bach', 'JSBach.jpg', 'special-lecture-all-about-js-bach', '<p><img src=\"/media/django-summernote/2023-06-15/9da8b1e7-1292-4424-9890-74d5df3cf0bb.jpg\" style=\"width: 640px;\"></p><h1 class=\"contactTitle\" style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; padding: 0px;\"><a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Georgia, serif; font-style: italic; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1em; color: rgb(87, 9, 19); font-size: 22px;\">The Family Tree of J. S. Bach</a>&nbsp;<div id=\"languageLinks\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; height: 20px; float: right;\"><p style=\"margin-bottom: 5px; padding: 0px; font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: 14px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; line-height: 1em; color: rgb(87, 9, 19); text-rendering: optimizelegibility; float: right;\"><br></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 5px; padding: 0px; font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: 14px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; line-height: 1em; color: rgb(87, 9, 19); text-rendering: optimizelegibility; float: right;\"><br></p></div></h1><p><img id=\"articleMainImg\" src=\"http://www.classichistory.net/images/Archives/bachFamilyTreeArchives/bachTreeImg.jpg\" alt=\"J. S. Bach family tree icon\" itemprop=\"image\" style=\"margin: 0px 20px 5px 0px; padding: 0px; width: 200px; height: 150px; float: left;\"></p><div class=\"contactContent\" itemprop=\"articleBody\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><p itemprop=\"description\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1.5em; padding: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.5em; font-family: Georgia, serif; color: rgb(28, 28, 28); text-rendering: optimizelegibility;\">While it is difficult to give any one definitive reason for the achievements of individuals in the Bach family, there certainly are many factors which worked in their favor. Most notably they all possessed a determined spirit that thrived on adversity. And so it happened that during one of the most tragic periods of German history that the Bachs were able to accomplish outstanding musical achievements. The strong solidarity of their family ties were incredibly helpful as well. Also, they often married into families who were themselves musically inclined, mixing the creative talent of many sources.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1.5em; padding: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.5em; font-family: Georgia, serif; color: rgb(28, 28, 28); text-rendering: optimizelegibility;\">Among J. S. Bach\'s close relatives there were some very talented composers. However his own father did not exhibit any creative gifts, and this was probably true of his grandfather, Christoph Bach, as well. Therefore it seems as though the musical talent inherited from his father\'s side accumulated in two generations before bursting forth.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1.5em; padding: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.5em; font-family: Georgia, serif; color: rgb(28, 28, 28); text-rendering: optimizelegibility;\">Although Bach\'s mother died when he was 10 years old, she was still a very important influence on him. The importance of his mother\'s family is shown by one fact in particular. His father, Johann Ambrosius, had a twin brother, Johann Christoph. These twins were so alike that even their own wives could not tell the two of them apart. And as musicians they were said to be nearly identical. Yet their children\'s musical talent shows no comparison. Christoph\'s son was an organist of mediocre talent, while J. S. Bach grew into a musical genius.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1.5em; padding: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.5em; font-family: Georgia, serif; color: rgb(28, 28, 28); text-rendering: optimizelegibility;\">Bach\'s children seem to have inherited their parents\' passion for music as well. A genius does not necessarily produce children with equally creative gifts. But in spite of J. S. Bach\'s enormous contributions to music, two of his sons became leaders in the music of their time, while two others themselves seem to have showed substantial musical talent.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1.5em; padding: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.5em; font-family: Georgia, serif; color: rgb(28, 28, 28); text-rendering: optimizelegibility;\">Below is a brief family tree for Johann Sebastian Bach. No attempt at completeness has been made, however what is shown has been diligently researched.</p><div class=\"W640H1380Img\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/creativeWork\" style=\"margin: 0px auto 30px; padding: 0px; width: 640px; float: none;\"><img src=\"http://www.classichistory.net/images/Archives/bachFamilyTreeArchives/bachFamilyTree.jpg\" alt=\"J. S. Bach family tree\" itemprop=\"image\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; width: 640px; height: 1380px; display: block; float: none;\"></div></div>', '2023-06-15 19:26:37.000000', '2023-06-15 19:29:50.147403', '2024-07-29 19:44:25.265439', 'published', 1);
