(13, 'Effective Witticisms', 'List-of-Idioms.jpg', 'effective-witticisms', '<p class=\"read\" style=\"margin: 0in; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><img src=\"/media/django-summernote/2024-07-29/12d088cf-691e-4900-be25-989cb7ca9c31.jpg\" style=\"width: 698px;\"><br></p><p class=\"read\" style=\"margin: 0in; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: &quot;Pretendard Variable&quot;, serif; font-size: 18px; letter-spacing: -0.133333px;\">Popular Phrases</span><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:&quot;Pretendard Variable&quot;,serif;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:Helvetica;color:black;letter-spacing:-.1pt\">\r\n<!--[if !supportLineBreakNewLine]--><br>\r\n<!--[endif]--><span style=\"word-spacing: 0.28px;\"></span><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans-serif;color:#333333\"></span><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"read\" style=\"margin: 0in; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:&quot;Pretendard Variable&quot;,serif;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:Helvetica;color:black;letter-spacing:-.1pt\"><span style=\"word-spacing: 0.28px;\">A Korean compatriot passed\r\nalong a proverb to the rather arrogant doctor: ‘The more ripe the rice, the\r\nmore it bows its head.’ Fortunately, he used the English expression ‘The boughs\r\nthat bear most hang lowest.’ Bough is a tree branch, and \'The boughs that bear\r\nmost\' means \'The branch that bears the most fruit is heavy and hangs low,\'\r\nwhich is consistent with the Korean concept of ripe rice. However, the doctor\r\nwho heard this is said to have said, ‘I’m not young enough to know everything.’\r\nand then responded, ‘When the apple is ripe, it will fall.’ The former is a\r\nliteral translation of ‘I am not young enough to know everything,’ and is a\r\nquote from Oscar Wilde, who liked cynical remarks. The actual meaning is that\r\nyoung people think they know everything, and for older people, it means that\r\neven though they are older, they don\'t know everything. The second sentence\r\nmeans that apples fall when ripe, but it is a counterattack by saying that it\r\nis good to hang low, but that you do not want to hang low.</span></span><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"read\" style=\"margin: 0in; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:&quot;Pretendard Variable&quot;,serif;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:Helvetica;color:black;letter-spacing:-.1pt\"><br>\r\n<!--[if !supportLineBreakNewLine]--><br>\r\n<!--[endif]--><span style=\"word-spacing: 0.28px;\"></span><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans-serif;color:#333333\"></span><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"read\" style=\"margin: 0in; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:&quot;Pretendard Variable&quot;,serif;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:Helvetica;color:black;letter-spacing:-.1pt\"><span style=\"word-spacing: 0.28px;\">‘The boughs that beat most\r\nhand lowest’ is the same as ‘Those who achieve are most unassuming.’ The former\r\nway of speaking is more effective. You can also increase the effectiveness of\r\nyour words by using unusual metaphors. Saying ‘He has Van Gogh’s ear for\r\nmusic.’ means ‘He has Van Gogh’s ears,’ but it implies that the painter Van\r\nGogh’s ears are illiterate in music. It\'s not much, but saying \'We live in a\r\nsociety where pizza gets to your house before the police\' makes fun of the\r\npolice. ‘Women might be able to fake orgasms. The expression ‘But men can fake\r\na whole relationship.’ means that men are better at lying. When a discussion\r\ndevelops into a heated argument and there are sharp differences of opinion,\r\nsome people end it with ‘If I agreed with you we’d both be wrong.’ Rather than\r\nusing similar expressions such as ‘Let’s agree to differ.’ or ‘I agree to\r\ndisagree.’ The effect is better.</span></span><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"read\" style=\"margin: 0in; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; word-spacing: 0.28px;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:&quot;Pretendard Variable&quot;,serif;\r\ncolor:black;letter-spacing:-.1pt\">&nbsp;</span></p><p class=\"read\" style=\"margin: 0in; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; word-spacing: 0.28px;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:&quot;Pretendard Variable&quot;,serif;\r\ncolor:black;letter-spacing:-.1pt\">&nbsp;</span></p><p class=\"read\" style=\"margin: 0in; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; word-spacing: 0.28px;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:&quot;Pretendard Variable&quot;,serif;\r\ncolor:black;letter-spacing:-.1pt\">Popular Phrases<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"read\" style=\"margin: 0in; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; word-spacing: 0.28px;\"><span lang=\"KO\" style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:&quot;맑은 고딕&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\r\n&quot;맑은 고딕&quot;;color:black;letter-spacing:-.1pt\">다소</span><span lang=\"KO\" style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:&quot;Pretendard Variable&quot;,serif;color:black;\r\nletter-spacing:-.1pt\"> </span><span lang=\"KO\" style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:\r\n&quot;맑은 고딕&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;맑은 고딕&quot;;color:black;letter-spacing:-.1pt\">거만한</span><span lang=\"KO\" style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:&quot;Pretendard Variable&quot;,serif;\r\ncolor:black;letter-spacing:-.1pt\"> </span><span lang=\"KO\" style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\r\nfont-family:&quot;맑은 고딕&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;맑은 고딕&quot;;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-.1pt\">의사에게</span><span lang=\"KO\" style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:&quot;Pretendard Variable&quot;,serif;\r\ncolor:black;letter-spacing:-.1pt\"> </span><span lang=\"KO\" style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\r\nfont-family:&quot;맑은 고딕&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;맑은 고딕&quot;;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-.1pt\">한국인</span><span lang=\"KO\" style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:&quot;Pretendard Variable&quot;,serif;\r\ncolor:black;letter-spacing:-.1pt\"> </span><span lang=\"KO\" style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\r\nfont-family:&quot;맑은 고딕&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;맑은 고딕&quot;;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-.1pt\">동포가</span><span lang=\"KO\" style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:&quot;Pretendard Variable&quot;,serif;\r\ncolor:black;letter-spacing:-.1pt\"> </span><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\r\nfont-family:&quot;Cambria&quot;,serif;mso-bidi-font-family:Cambria;color:blac